abstract: Officials took the unusual step of distributing his photo, asking the public for help in finding him.
snippet: Officials took the unusual step of distributing his photo, asking the public for help in finding him.
lead_paragraph: Nine days after a Barnard student was killed during a mugging in a park, New York City police on Friday were carrying out an extensive manhunt for a 14-year-old boy who detectives believed may have been the one who stabbed her with a knife.

abstract: House Democrats asked for documents from federal prosecutors and Florida law enforcement officials on Friday as part of a probe into how financier Jeffrey Epstein received a secret plea deal more than a decade ago after he was accused of molesting underage girls.
snippet: House Democrats asked for documents from federal prosecutors and Florida law enforcement officials on Friday as part of a probe into how financier Jeffrey Epstein received a secret plea deal more than a decade ago after he was accused of molesting...
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — House Democrats asked for documents from federal prosecutors and Florida law enforcement officials on Friday as part of a probe into how financier Jeffrey Epstein received a secret plea deal more than a decade ago after he was accused of molesting underage girls.
headline_main: House Asks for Documents in Epstein Probe From DOJ
headline_print_headline: House Asks for Documents in Epstein Probe From DOJ

abstract: Other legal academics took issue with his view that impeachment only happens when the House transmits its charges to the Senate.
snippet: Other legal academics took issue with his view that impeachment only happens when the House transmits its charges to the Senate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Maybe President Trump has not been impeached after all, or at least not yet.

abstract: Robert Glenn “Junior” Johnson, the moonshine runner turned NASCAR driver described as “The Last American Hero” by author Tom Wolfe in a 1965 article for Esquire, died Friday. He was 88.

abstract: Amid fallout from a scathing inspector general report, the court that oversees national security surveillance is also getting a new presiding judge.
snippet: Amid fallout from a scathing inspector general report, the court that oversees national security surveillance is also getting a new presiding judge.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A secretive court that oversees national security surveillance has taken a step toward addressing dysfunction in the system detailed in a recent inspector general report, ordering the Justice Department to identify all cases that an F.B.I. lawyer heavily criticized in the report has worked on, according to an order made public on Friday.

abstract: Being with people you love becomes more important than small digs and even arguing about Donald Trump.
snippet: Being with people you love becomes more important than small digs and even arguing about Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: Anyone desperate enough to Google the term “holiday stress” will be rewarded (or become more overwhelmed) with about 395,000,000 results. Limit the search to “holiday stress statistics 2019” and the results come down to a measly 28,100,000 or so. There are even specific memes and GIFs on how to handle the financial, social and emotional stresses of the season, including my current favorite, the article that ran in this newspaper by a Buddhist teacher who advises practicing “acceptance,” an activity that even on nonholidays can often seem as challenging as climbing Mount Everest in an ice storm.

abstract: “No one should be made to feel uncomfortable or be discriminated against because of their natural hair,” Gov. Phil Murphy said.
snippet: “No one should be made to feel uncomfortable or be discriminated against because of their natural hair,” Gov. Phil Murphy said.
lead_paragraph: One year after a black high school wrestler in New Jersey was forced to cut his dreadlocks to participate in a match, Gov. Phil Murphy signed a law this week making it illegal to discriminate against people based on hairstyles associated with race.
